Theory Seminar, 19 Nov 2010 CS 269S, Fall 2010: Theory Seminar CS Building, Room 243 19 Nov 2010: Succinct Convex Greedy Drawing of 3-Connected Plane Graphs Lowell Trott The authors show that the classical Schnyder drawing in R2 of 3-connected plane graphs is weakly greedy with respect to a metric function H(*,*). The drawing is planar, convex, and succinct, using two integer coordinates between 0 and f, where f is the number of internal faces of the graph. (Based on a paper by He and Zhang to appear at SODA 2011.)